<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79e72940-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s4007"><num value="4007">§ 4007.</num><heading> Voluntary payments</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any person may make voluntary payments to assist the National Council to carry out its annual marketing and promotion plan and annual budget. The Secretary shall deposit such payments into the Fund.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79e72941-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/99/659/tII/s208">Pub. L. 99–659, title II, § 208</ref>, <date date="1986-11-14">Nov. 14, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3720">100 Stat. 3720</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
